Forgot what a process it was to create a rest api from scratch :joy:

This might be a big mistake
Keep in mind a lot of the stuff we rely on today are rails apps for a reason
I've already created multiple rest api's from before when we've had uni projects
But that was with Hibernat e:P

it's 2016 dude, you need a dockerized microservice *per* api call!
atm I have a business layer for all database trafic and I just use that layer in the rest api
Control is overrated. You need to understand that having too much control is sometimes just as bad as having no control
